function OnClickUp() UIComponent(this:Parent()):LuaCall("Notify", Component.Messages.StateChange, this:CurrentState(), Address) end

local this = UIComponent(Address)

function OnSelect() local parent = UIComponent(UIComponent(Address):Parent())
parent:LuaCall("RemoveSelected") end

local parent = UIComponent(UIComponent(Address):Parent(3))
function OnSelect() parent:LuaCall("SelectOption", Address) end

uientry.unicode: Toggle display of "classic" battles.||Classic battles use clan unit rosters and are unranked.
This column shows whether a game is open, closed or in-progress.||Click the column header to sort games by status.

This column enables players to search for games by name.||You can sort this list alphabetically by clicking on the column header. ||Sometimes the host will have specific rules, such as 'no cavalry', or 'beginners only' and mention them in the game name.||You can search for preferences like these in the Search box.
Use this column to find your preferred battle type.||Click the column header to sort games by battle type.
Use this column to find your favourite map, or perhaps new ones you have yet to play.||Click the column header to sort games by map.
This column shows a game's connection status.||Click the column header to sort games by connection status.
Funds affect the quality and number of units you can buy.||Click the column header to sort games by funds.
This column shows the number of players needed for each game.||You can choose to fight an eight player match, or you may want a one-on-one.||Click the column header to sort games by player numbers.
This column shows how many of your friends are in a game.||Click the column header to sort games by this number.

This shows the average XP of the players in each game.||Pick a battle with an average XP similar to yours, or challenge yourself by fighting against more experienced players.||Click the header to sort games by average XP.
